    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Uniforms in the Closet</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Larry Armstrong letter on Jennifer Egan's June 28 article holds homosexuals in armed forces deserve respect; photo</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Anyone who has ever been in the service knows there is one person in the military you can discriminate against: a coward. In a two-year hitch in the Army I never saw any cowards, and I certainly saw none in your article. The soldiers and sailors in your story wear the same uniform, take the same risks and salute the same flag we all do. What they deserve is our respect.</p>
        <p>Larry Armstrong</p>
        <p>Spokane, Wash.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
